    {
      "id": "PopularPost26513",
      "post_content": "Fictionarious, the revised Oracle text says \"at the beginning of the upkeep\", and the untap step doesn't exist. Each turn begins with the beginning of the upkeep (unless it ceases to exist too: [Eon Hub](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Eon Hub)), but it's irrelevant to my question: *does a Sands of Time that comes into play \"at the beginning of the upkeep\" (e.g. via [Braids, Conjurer Adept](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Braids, Conjurer Adept)) trigger in the same upkeep or only on the next turn's upkeep?*   \nThe rules aren't very clear on \"the beginning of the upkeep\" being a state (a piece of the upkeep) or an event (the transition between whatever comes before, either the draw step or the previous turn or something else, and the upkeep).  \n  \nMy favorite combinations are with [Capsize](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Capsize) (beyond one Capsize per turn, and it's easy to play 2-3, it's usually game over), [Prodigal Sorcerer](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Prodigal Sorcerer)/[Zuran Spellcaster](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Zuran Spellcaster)/[Reveka, Wizard Savant](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Reveka, Wizard Savant) etc. for creature extermination and ... [(see all)](javascript:void(0);)",
      "posted_by": "LG",
      "html": "<div class=\"post oddItem\" id=\"PopularPost26513\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl07_post\">Fictionarious, the revised Oracle text says \"at the beginning of the upkeep\", and the untap step doesn't exist. Each turn begins with the beginning of the upkeep (unless it ceases to exist too: <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Eon Hub\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Eon Hub\">Eon Hub</a>), but it's irrelevant to my question: <i>does a Sands of Time that comes into play \"at the beginning of the upkeep\" (e.g. via <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Braids, Conjurer Adept\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Braids, Conjurer Adept\">Braids, Conjurer Adept</a>) trigger in the same upkeep or only on the next turn's upkeep? </i><br/>The rules aren't very clear on \"the beginning of the upkeep\" being a state (a piece of the upkeep) or an event (the transition between whatever comes before, either the draw step or the previous turn or something else, and the upkeep).<br/><br/>My favorite combinations are with <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Capsize\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Capsize\">Capsize</a> (beyond one Capsize per turn, and it's easy to play 2-3, it's usually game over), <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Prodigal Sorcerer\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Prodigal Sorcerer\">Prodigal Sorcerer</a>/<a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Zuran Spellcaster\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Zuran Spellcaster\">Zuran Spellcaster</a>/<a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Reveka, Wizard Savant\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Reveka, Wizard Savant\">Reveka, Wizard Savant</a> etc. for creature extermination and ... <a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" onclick=\"ExpandPost(event, this, 26513)\">(see all)</a></span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl07_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"http://wizards.custhelp.com/cgi-bin/wizards.cfg/php/enduser/ask.php?p_prods=522,706,739&amp;p_cats=\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl07_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '26513'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Posted By: \r\n                                <span id=\"PostedBy10016\">LG</span>\r\n                                (11/9/2009 6:00:02 AM)\r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    Rating:\u00a0\r\n                                </div>\n<div style=\"float: left;\">\n<div class=\"starRating\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl07_postRating_starRating\"><img alt=\"0.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"1.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"1.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"2.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"2.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"3.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightSolidSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"3.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"4.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"4.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"5.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/>\n<br/>\n</div>\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    \u00a0\r\n                                </div>\n<div style=\"float: left;\">\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n</div>\n<br class=\"cl